    <text>
        <body>
            <head>5. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassies in <placeName
                    corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">France</placeName>, <placeName
                    corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italy</placeName>, and <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d5fn1">Source: National Archives, RG
                    59, Central Foreign Policy File, D770116–0033. Secret; Priority; <gloss
                        target="#t_Exdis_1">Exdis</gloss>. Sent for information to Algiers, Baghdad,
                    Jidda, London, Oslo, Rabat, Tripoli, <gloss target="#t_USUN_1">USUN</gloss>, the
                    Secretary of Defense, <gloss target="#t_CINCUSNAVEUR_1">CINCUSNAVEUR</gloss>,
                        <gloss target="#t_COMSIXTHFLT_1">COMSIXTHFLT</gloss>, <gloss
                        target="#t_EUCOM_1">EUCOM</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_USDOCOSOUTH_1"
                        >USDOCOSOUTH</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="recSv8kXhhqWsvvbj"
                        >Wilkinson</persName>; cleared in draft in EUR and <gloss target="#t_IO_1"
                        >IO</gloss>; approved by <persName corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu"
                        >Atherton</persName>.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1977-04-02T22:37:00+00:00">April 2, 1977, 2237Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>73662. Subject: <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj"
                    >Tunisian</placeName>-<placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="reczz1d8j78JEEJZg">Shelf</rs>
                <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recvVLlMQyjpyiiF9">Dispute</rs>: <persName
                    corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName>-<persName
                    corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> Meeting on April 1. <gloss
                    target="#t_CINCUSNAVEUR_1">CINCUSNAVEUR</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_EUCOM_1"
                    >EUCOM</gloss> pass <gloss target="#t_POLAD_1">POLADs</gloss>. USDOCOSOUTH pass
                CINCSOUTH for <gloss target="#t_POLAD_1">POLAD</gloss>. Ref: State 71629.<note n="2"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d5fn2">See <ref target="#d4fn5">footnote 5, Document
                        4</ref>.</note>
            </p>
            <pb facs="0032" n="11" xml:id="pg_11"/>
            <p>1. Summary: After reviewing background on <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libyan</placeName>-<placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisian</placeName>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="reczz1d8j78JEEJZg">shelf</rs>
                <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recvVLlMQyjpyiiF9">dispute</rs>, <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisian</placeName> Ambassador <persName
                    corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> and Assistant Secretary <persName
                    corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName> discussed ways in which U.S.
                might help Tunisians in their effort to resolve <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recvVLlMQyjpyiiF9">dispute</rs> by peaceful means. <persName
                    corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName> drew on points in guidance sent
                    <gloss target="#t_septel_1">septel</gloss>
                <note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d5fn3">See <ref target="#d4fn6">footnote 6,
                        Document 4</ref>.</note> and added that we would discuss issue with
                    <placeName corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">France</placeName> and <placeName
                    corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italy</placeName>. End summary.</p>
            <p>2. <persName corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName>’s report on situation
                paralleled full reports from Embassy Tunis, including <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>’s threat to <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisian</placeName>
                <gloss target="#t_FonMin_1">FonMin</gloss>
                <persName corresp="recJ2LgM5qsYgq9Dd">Chatty</persName> in Tripoli last week.
                    <persName corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> added that <persName
                    corresp="recJ2LgM5qsYgq9Dd">Chatty</persName> had spent this week travelling to
                capitals to see Fahmi and Fahd and Iraqi Representative, probably Hammadi, returning
                to Tunis on March 31. Tunisians had repeatedly asked Italians to comply with their
                earlier promises about withdrawal of drilling rig, and had sought <placeName
                    corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">French</placeName> support as well. <persName
                    corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> suggested that U.S. might also
                intercede with <placeName corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">France</placeName> and
                    <placeName corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italy</placeName>.</p>
            <p>3. <persName corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName> reassured <persName
                    corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> that we would help in <orgName
                    corresp="recI8JFNFTJYHnXbK">Security Council</orgName>, if necessary, and
                suggested that <placeName corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisian</placeName>
                <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> Mission talk to SYG <persName
                    corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName>. <persName
                    corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> took occasion to ask for increased
                U.S. <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB">military assistance</rs>,
                including Redeye. <persName corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName> replied
                that no assurances on increased <rs type="topic" corresp="recoKawZ2IOcE8nyB"
                    >military assistance</rs> were possible at the moment. In any event, <placeName
                    corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName> appeared more in need of
                diplomatic support from friends. In this regard, he said we would exchange views
                with <placeName corresp="recJuFaVGGmK95QOO">France</placeName> and <placeName
                    corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italy</placeName>.</p>
            <p>4. <persName corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> said this would be helpful
                particularly in Rome, where Tunis by itself could scarcely compete with <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>, given important <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>-<placeName
                    corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italian</placeName> economic links. Speaking without
                instructions, he asked the U.S. to give consideration to what further steps could be
                taken in the event that <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>
                should continue to push Tunisians toward the wall. He specifically recalled U.S.
                political/military support in August 1976 (extended <orgName
                    corresp="recAmXuDx0uJUNDQN">Sixth Fleet</orgName> ship visit, birthday message
                from President <persName corresp="recndPfEY7jX792yL">Ford</persName>, exchange of
                intelligence, etc.), and linked support from U.S. and others to <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>’s agreement only a few weeks
                later to submit issue to <gloss target="#t_ICJ_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recnz5VXG29Ke5gek">ICJ</orgName>
                </gloss>.</p>
            <p>5. Comment: Neither <persName corresp="reclCf8vZH8axhvIA">Hedda</persName> nor
                    <persName corresp="recqQ6Wv2eONUThFu">Atherton</persName> was aware at time of
                meeting of information in report being repeated <gloss target="#t_septel_1"
                    >septel</gloss> that <placeName corresp="rec9ITG67JtRs3uBT">Italian</placeName>
                rig <rs type="topic" corresp="reckICv61aFkmqwBF">Scarabeo </rs>has apparently moved
                to east out of disputed area. Although this will help to defuse situation, we do not
                yet know whether Tunisians will wish to continue to press for <gloss
                    target="#t_SC_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recI8JFNFTJYHnXbK">SC</orgName>
                </gloss> consideration of issue. Mere removal of rig does not resolve <persName
                    corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName>’s backtracking on August 1976
                agreement to submit matter to Hague, nor his threatening demand that operations in
                Isis field to the north be suspended.</p>
            <pb facs="0033" n="12" xml:id="pg_12"/>
            <p>6. For Rome and Paris: We will forward instructions and talking points <gloss
                    target="#t_septel_1">septel</gloss> for discussions with FonMins on <rs
                    type="topic" corresp="reczz1d8j78JEEJZg">shelf</rs> issue.<note n="4"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d5fn4">In telegram 80407 to Rome, Paris, and London, April
                    10, the Department transmitted the following instructions: “You should inform
                        <gloss target="#t_FonOff_1">FonOff</gloss> that U.S. is concerned about
                    possible threat to the peace as a result of recent <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> statements re disputed <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="reczz1d8j78JEEJZg">shelf</rs> area between <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> and <placeName
                        corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>. You should state that we
                    are following standard policy of not taking a position on legal merits of a <rs
                        type="compound-subject" corresp="recvVLlMQyjpyiiF9">dispute</rs> to which we
                    are not parties and advising American drillers to stay out of disputed waters,
                    but we are willing to associate ourselves with <placeName
                        corresp="recGkuSlDiu6KVzHj">Tunisia</placeName>’s efforts to prevent the
                    matter from being settled by force. You should note that Tunisians have been
                    eager to drill an exploratory well in disputed zone for over a year, but are
                    continuing to exercise restraint and avoid provoking Libyans. Libyans, in
                    contrast, have exercised no such restraint.” (National Archives, RG 59, Central
                    Foreign Policy File, D770124–1218)</note>
            </p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Vance</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
